<promed@promedmail.org>
[It should be noted that the United Kingdom's Ministry of Agriculture
Fisheries and Food suffered similar embarrassment when it was found that,
in spite of government regulations, cross-contamination and usages
continued. This was reported a number of years before the French government
implemented similar restrictions. There was adequate warning.
Coincidentally, the EU has released the report on organic fertilizers
derived from ruminant animals: Opinion of the Scientific Steering Committee:
<http://europa.eu.int/comm/food/fs/sc/ssc/out205_en.pdf>
